  {
    "id": "bfad1a5d-305b-46df-b462-b976171a99db",
    "sentence": "Almost all participants cited a number of recent events as indicative of tighter financial conditions in the United States; these events included declines in equity prices, a widening in credit spreads, a further rise in the exchange value of the dollar, and an increase in financial market volatility.",
    "source": "minutes_20160127.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
