    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bdf0f93c-0159-41d3-9da2-0733341c4329",
    "sentence": "The deputy manager followed with a discussion of money markets and open market operations.",
    "source": "minutes_20180801.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180801",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f18d5afa-49f4-4e2d-8a0c-3c4be5814a7f",
    "sentence": "In assessing recent developments in financial market conditions, participants referred to the continued low level of longer-term interest rates, in particular those on U.S Treasury securities.",
    "source": "minutes_20170726.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170726",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3fea32b6-6372-4ff1-852f-da387a2c2ac8",
    "sentence": "The policy rate path derived from futures prices and the modal path derived from options prices both declined over the intermeeting period and had come into closer alignment with the median of the modal responses from the Open Market Desk's Survey of Primary Dealers and Survey of Market Participants.",
    "source": "minutes_20240731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e95ab7c9-29de-4a26-ad38-11db2df562bd",
    "sentence": "Noting the increase in uncertainty about the economic outlook over the intermeeting period, several participants suggested that additional accommodation could be required to promote economic recovery and return inflation to the Committee's 2 percent objective.",
    "source": "minutes_20200729.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200729",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9b9459cd-015e-4531-b911-ebc0fb2cede2",
    "sentence": "Labor productivity growth appeared to have remained slow over the four quarters ending in the first quarter of this year.",
    "source": "minutes_20160427.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dd39e729-46cb-403b-b44d-0caab7d73c41",
    "sentence": "Housing starts and construction permits moved up in November and December and finished the year well above their pre‑pandemic levels.",
    "source": "minutes_20210127.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210127",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3c2e275f-c2b8-4b49-96b0-14030351059c",
    "sentence": "Participants indicated that the Committee, in making policy decisions over the next few years, should conduct policy with the aim of keeping inflation near its longer-run symmetric objective while sustaining the economic expansion and a strong labor market.",
    "source": "minutes_20180502.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180502",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "99490df5-8fa7-48fa-acde-ee6fbd9ef9bd",
    "sentence": "The employment cost index for total labor compensation in the private sector increased 2.8 percent over the 12 months ending in March -- a period mostly predating the onset of the pandemic -- and was the same as its year-earlier pace.",
    "source": "minutes_20200610.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200610",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "11606546-efd4-4cb7-b628-5307a9e01f27",
    "sentence": "In recent months, however, the pace of improvement had moderated, with slower growth expected for the fourth quarter.",
    "source": "minutes_20201105.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20201105",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "829cb089-3fff-4abf-b4d9-9bc9660b8cd0",
    "sentence": "In light of the prominent risks to the Committee's objectives with respect to both maximum employment and price stability, participants generally noted the importance of closely monitoring incoming information and its implications for the economic outlook.",
    "source": "minutes_20230503.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230503",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "434b7423-38f7-44ff-861f-938f0d69ce37",
    "sentence": "Data for February showed a wider nominal U.S. international trade deficit than in January.",
    "source": "minutes_20210428.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210428",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2b0a6283-9037-4119-90ed-b52f31613c15",
    "sentence": "Accordingly, not only would a reduction be appropriate in light of the ongoing improvement in labor market conditions, but it also would support the credibility and predictability of monetary policy because it would be seen as following through on the Committee's earlier communications about the outlook for the asset purchase program.",
    "source": "minutes_20130918.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "adf2e6c1-73b0-4bb2-92f4-8486c8ee53e2",
    "sentence": "However, the recovery was viewed as unevenly distributed across industries.",
    "source": "minutes_20200916.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200916",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c79c1a6e-3a86-4aaf-a638-fc93336cb953",
    "sentence": "Several participants discussed the importance of communicating that the ongoing reduction in the Federal Reserve's balance sheet could continue for some time even as the Committee reduced its target range for the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "minutes_20240918.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "821f86d3-e4ae-49aa-9b8d-858f31dd4fa8",
    "sentence": "A couple of participants noted that inflation expectations would likely be influenced by the behavior of the overall inflation rate, inclusive of the effects of tariffs.",
    "source": "minutes_20250730.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20250730",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6ec82694-0f15-41ee-b8ff-f470ee0971f3",
    "sentence": "Virus-sensitive sectors and firms with weaker fundamentals underperformed over the period, as they had over the broader pandemic episode.",
    "source": "minutes_20200729.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200729",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f8252fbd-412e-4bb7-afc2-467c628cdd0c",
    "sentence": "Participants expected that real GDP growth this year would be below the strong pace recorded in 2023, and they remarked that recent data on economic activity were largely consistent with the anticipated slowing.",
    "source": "minutes_20240612.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240612",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "462bb331-fe72-4576-9f94-45268abd8536",
    "sentence": "The staff continued to forecast that real GDP would expand at a modestly faster pace than potential output in 2016 through 2018, supported primarily by increases in consumer spending. The unemployment rate was expected to remain relatively flat over the second half of the year and then to gradually decline further; over this period, the unemployment rate was projected to run somewhat below the staff's estimate of its longer-run natural rate.",
    "source": "minutes_20160615.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2c56c4c4-d2b7-43c4-bb22-1a2d70a814d3",
    "sentence": "Expectations for near-term domestic policy easing had occurred against the backdrop of a global shift toward more accommodative monetary policy.",
    "source": "minutes_20190731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1246b8e9-7224-40bc-bbf6-6fc4ef19a93e",
    "sentence": "Nonfinancial firms continued to issue debt at a strong pace over the period.",
    "source": "minutes_20120801.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120801",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4106d80e-02a5-4d36-b2ed-c9bd5ea544aa",
    "sentence": "Consumer spending continued to advance, but spending on items other than motor vehicles was relatively soft.",
    "source": "minutes_20130731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "76115bfe-9da1-4f7e-a52f-67911fed7d4d",
    "sentence": "Participants observed that recent inflation had been higher and more persistent than anticipated.",
    "source": "minutes_20221102.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bcd88c01-f433-4393-8ffd-a4053ff170cb",
    "sentence": "Several participants noted that if the economy evolved along the lines of their current outlooks, then further policy firming after this meeting may not be necessary.",
    "source": "minutes_20230503.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230503",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f1a11d41-701d-4e6b-9b36-f7372194e474",
    "sentence": "More recently, the energy sector had come under stress.",
    "source": "minutes_20200315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "df79a5d8-4970-420c-b7ae-b66a8bc0a727",
    "sentence": "Dolmas, Economic Policy Advisor and Senior Economist, Federal Reserve Bank of Dallas",
    "source": "minutes_20220727.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220727",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
