    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2a510d68-882f-45f6-98c7-6917693642e2",
    "sentence": "However, some noted that their forecasts were now consistent with a shallower path than they had expected at the time of the March meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20160615.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ae7567d4-7888-4584-8d31-bb1432861d31",
    "sentence": "The need to use a range of indicators to gauge labor market conditions was noted.",
    "source": "minutes_20130320.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d07b6f18-6c1f-40d1-a715-e5d1b9a241f7",
    "sentence": "Market turmoil spilled into municipal bond markets late in the intermeeting period, as spreads widened substantially and some borrowers became hesitant to come to the market.",
    "source": "minutes_20200315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a26a0ae2-55f1-4b95-920f-8238bfe9c3ca",
    "sentence": "The revision reflected the apparent decline in federal defense purchases and the somewhat shallower trajectory for consumer spending in recent months; the recent data on the labor market, production, and other spending categories were, on balance, roughly in line with the staff's expectations at the time of the previous forecast.",
    "source": "minutes_20120125.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120125",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2e17253d-8da1-489d-8a11-e75b861daeb7",
    "sentence": "In the Survey of Market Participants, the median investor's modal path for the federal funds rate also moved down substantially, while in the Survey of Primary Dealers, the median dealer's modal path was little changed.",
    "source": "minutes_20160427.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a7abcc5b-396b-4484-b452-067f313a023c",
    "sentence": "The calendar of repo operations starting in mid-January could reflect a gradual reduction in active repo operations.",
    "source": "minutes_20191211.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20191211",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6c95f2c9-3946-4d8c-9f10-b60f47b51af6",
    "sentence": "In determining the extent to which additional policy firming may be appropriate to return inflation to 2 percent over time, members concurred that they will take into account the cumulative tightening of monetary policy, the lags with which monetary policy affects economic activity and inflation, and economic and financial developments.",
    "source": "minutes_20230503.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230503",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5cfe9286-bc9c-4f93-949d-44bb56b63917",
    "sentence": "Multiple recent surveys, including the Senior Loan Officer Opinion Survey on Bank Lending Practices and the Kansas City Fed's Small Business Lending Survey, suggested that lending standards had remained relatively tight for small businesses through December.",
    "source": "minutes_20250319.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20250319",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8238e686-b34c-4e62-86b0-e0c1caa4487e",
    "sentence": "Participants pointed to various risks to economic activity and employment, including downside risks associated with weaker output growth abroad, increased financial vulnerabilities stemming from overvaluation of risky assets, or an unexpected weakening of the labor market, and upside risks associated with increased optimism and continued strength in domestic spending as upside factors.",
    "source": "minutes_20241218.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20241218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8d38f867-d278-44b5-9106-372f4f5b049c",
    "sentence": "Some other participants, however, remarked that al­though inflationary pressures were lasting longer than anticipated, those pressures continued to reflect the same pandemic-related imbalances and would likely abate when supply constraints eased.",
    "source": "minutes_20211103.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20211103",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "98c73c3c-c373-438f-a8bb-852f8a98a942",
    "sentence": "In particular, participants saw the economic outlook as little changed or modestly improved relative to the December meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20130130.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130130",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2bc51695-11c6-497d-a3e1-0f6f6f4ba7f0",
    "sentence": "Many participants noted that the Committee's credibility with regard to bringing inflation back to the 2 percent objective, together with previous communications, had been helpful in shifting market expectations of future policy and had already contributed to a notable tightening of financial conditions that would likely help reduce inflation pressures by restraining aggregate demand.",
    "source": "minutes_20220615.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5a48a8ef-f66d-4d35-8cb2-855f35b25d4c",
    "sentence": "But many anticipated that further efforts to implement and perhaps to augment these policies would be necessary to fully resolve the area's fiscal and financial problems and commented that financial markets would remain focused on the situation in Europe as it evolves. It was noted that the changes to the central bank currency swap lines announced in late November helped to ease dollar funding conditions facing European institutions, but such conditions were still strained.",
    "source": "minutes_20111213.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20111213",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "af9b5f2e-4547-4906-8d22-1f80a9f61f1a",
    "sentence": "The broad dollar index was little changed over the intermeeting period.",
    "source": "minutes_20240731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a891a8fa-b493-49f9-a6a4-3d5714500037",
    "sentence": "Real residential investment declined further in the third quarter, likely reflecting a range of factors including the continued effects of rising mortgage interest rates on the affordability of housing.",
    "source": "minutes_20181108.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20181108",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3a1d5581-73c4-47ba-a6ca-ec83ec98cf7d",
    "sentence": "The staff judged that the ongoing war in Ukraine remained a possible source of even greater upward pressure on energy and commodity prices, while the war and adverse developments associated with China's zero-COVID policy were both perceived as increasing the risk that supply chain disruptions and production constraints would be further exacerbated in the United States and abroad.",
    "source": "minutes_20220615.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a422c9bf-36e7-4e71-a006-211618237414",
    "sentence": "Over the intermeeting period, spreads of yields on speculative-grade corporate bonds over those on comparable-maturity Treasury securities narrowed slightly, on net.",
    "source": "minutes_20210922.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210922",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f3260446-90b7-499f-b1a8-6b519a835407",
    "sentence": "Recent increases in consumer food and energy prices, together with the small uptick in core consumer price inflation, led the staff to raise its near-term projection for consumer price inflation.",
    "source": "minutes_20110427.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "961f3b62-5d88-4e23-9cca-7bec1dc40e84",
    "sentence": "Participants generally anticipated that inflation was likely to decline further in the near term, reflecting the reduction in oil prices and the effects of the rise in the foreign exchange value of the dollar on import prices.Most participants saw these influences as temporary and thus continued to expect inflation to move back gradually to the Committee's 2 percent longer-run objective as the labor market improved further in an environment of well-anchored inflation expectations.Survey-based measures of longer-term inflation expectations remained stable, although market-based measures of inflation compensation over the next five years, as well as over the five-year period beginning five years ahead, moved down further over the intermeeting period.Participants discussed various explanations for the decline in market-based measures, including a fall in expected future inflation, reductions in inflation risk premiums, and higher liquidity and other premiums that might be influencing the prices of Treasury Inflation-Protected Securities and inflation derivatives.Model-based decompositions of inflation compensation seemed to support the message from surveys that longer-term inflation expectations had remained stable, although it was observed that these results were sensitive to the assumptions underlying the particular models used.",
    "source": "minutes_20141217.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20141217",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "45c76dd3-c880-4325-82af-65d0c5aef987",
    "sentence": "Part of this projected increase in the rate of real GDP growth reflected the staff's expectation that the drag on economic growth from fiscal policy would be smaller in the second half as the pace of reductions in federal government purchases slowed and as the restraint on growth in consumer spending stemming from the higher taxes put in place at the beginning of the year diminished.",
    "source": "minutes_20130731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5210d93e-b817-4454-a2a9-fcd350b39fb2",
    "sentence": "Output increased markedly at both motor vehicle manufacturers and their upstream suppliers as the supply chain disruptions associated with the earthquake in Japan eased.",
    "source": "minutes_20110921.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110921",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a414d2a7-b559-4a75-ab16-92264fee3298",
    "sentence": "A few participants noted that national and District surveys of firms' capital spending plans suggested that the recent slowing in business fixed investment was partly temporary.",
    "source": "minutes_20120125.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120125",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d03009a0-7289-45a9-ac83-235599b2b92c",
    "sentence": "Incoming data suggested that foreign economic growth slowed further in the fourth quarter to a very subdued pace.",
    "source": "minutes_20200129.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200129",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2fe08c61-43ef-4be5-a852-60e296444872",
    "sentence": "A number of participants emphasized that it would be important to clearly communicate that a slowing in the pace of rate increases was not an indication of any weakening of the Committee's resolve to achieve its price-stability goal or a judgment that inflation was already on a persistent downward path.",
    "source": "minutes_20221214.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20221214",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ce6e348f-a09f-4e65-8351-22dabfa89d84",
    "sentence": "The staff's near-term projection for inflation was revised down from the forecast prepared for the April FOMC meeting, reflecting a greater-than-expected drop in consumer energy prices.",
    "source": "minutes_20120620.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120620",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a1f32397-cb11-48e5-ba52-b6af540bd78e",
    "sentence": "It was noted that the Committee would continue its deliberations on reinvestment policy during upcoming meetings and would release additional information as it becomes available. In that context, several participants indicated that, when the Committee announces its plans for a change to its reinvestment policy, it would be desirable to also provide more information to the public about the Committee's expectations for the size and composition of the Federal Reserve's assets and liabilities in the longer run.",
    "source": "minutes_20170315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "06b47770-34fe-44a3-95b2-3418fc2f0158",
    "sentence": "Over the next several months, seasonal fluctuations in nonreserve liabilities were projected to lead to significant declines in reserves at the end of December, in late January, and especially in mid-to-late April if securities holdings in the System Open Market Account (SOMA) were to remain unchanged.",
    "source": "minutes_20251210.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20251210",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7708cd37-072f-4d09-8762-14c867a11fd8",
    "sentence": "Similarly, GDP growth remained subdued in China and several other emerging economies in Asia, and indicators suggested that growth in Latin America also remained weak.",
    "source": "minutes_20191030.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20191030",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "38b37c49-b83b-4569-b5e3-0fdf4dba2aa8",
    "sentence": "In survey responses, market participants again reported elevated uncertainty about the outlook for U.S. economic policies and about financial asset prices, but various measures of implied volatility nonetheless declined further.",
    "source": "minutes_20170315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d8771aab-c5d1-4f03-879e-8711bd29304a",
    "sentence": "Regarding the business sector, a few participants noted that favorable aggregate supply developments -- including increases in labor supply, business investment, and productivity -- continued to support solid expansion of business activity.",
    "source": "minutes_20241107.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20241107",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "32d68177-9b2a-43bc-9ea1-33e291318153",
    "sentence": "The manager pro tem finished by noting that the Federal Reserve Bank of New York would soon release a request for public comment on a plan to publish a series of backward looking Secured Overnight Financing Rate (SOFR) averages and a daily SOFR index to support the transition away from instruments based on LIBOR (London interbank offered rate).",
    "source": "minutes_20191030.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20191030",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b56e8beb-3778-4638-9cc6-f7d608cc1724",
    "sentence": "The staff also discussed the potential implications of additional asset purchases for the evolution of the Federal Reserve's balance sheet and income.",
    "source": "minutes_20120913.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120913",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "27b94694-7faf-419b-8a82-99cd91d1677f",
    "sentence": "In their subsequent discussion, participants agreed that the Committee's testing of normalization tools, in conjunction with its other planning, had created conditions under which policy normalization would likely proceed smoothly once it commences.",
    "source": "minutes_20150429.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150429",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9464aebc-43e1-43f9-a958-1214b4a7efc1",
    "sentence": "Many participants saw significant downside risks to economic growth.",
    "source": "minutes_20110921.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110921",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5297e4ba-04b2-4b95-b413-7960e9a537f9",
    "sentence": "The consumer sentiment measure from the Michigan survey edged up in August, while the Conference Board survey measure moved down; both measures continued to be below their levels at the beginning of the year.",
    "source": "minutes_20200916.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200916",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4425cb28-392b-4038-a944-8fd340fcaa0a",
    "sentence": "Participants shared views on possible outcomes for the reopening of the economy, the prospects for effective voluntary social distancing, and the efficacy of public health initiatives for their implications for economic activity and employment.",
    "source": "minutes_20200610.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200610",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5a51e0f2-8f47-451e-883a-9fbfbe1e768d",
    "sentence": "The credit performance of corporate bonds and leveraged loans remained generally stable, though the default rate for leveraged loans that includes distressed exchanges continued to be elevated.",
    "source": "minutes_20250917.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20250917",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "080771ad-dbf9-49d2-8a07-019bdacccbcf",
    "sentence": "In their discussion of forward guidance about the target federal funds rate, a few members suggested that lowering the unemployment threshold to 6 percent could effectively convey the Committee's intention to keep the target federal funds rate low for an extended period.",
    "source": "minutes_20131218.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20131218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5c03bc70-05bd-4cf7-8784-8002e6ab4f84",
    "sentence": "The SOMA manager noted that survey responses suggested that the dispersion in views about the timing of a rate increase might be related to differing views about the economic conditions that would prevail when the FOMC first lifted the target range, as survey respondents' views about those conditions were also dispersed.",
    "source": "minutes_20200729.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200729",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8ae16cdf-8be5-4f70-a9b3-e519bce97389",
    "sentence": "Regarding banks, a couple of participants commented that, though regulatory capital levels remained strong, some banks continued to be vulnerable to a rise in longer-term yields and the associated unrealized losses on bank assets.",
    "source": "minutes_20250730.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20250730",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dd2af560-0cd9-4ffa-8f2b-e6036c823313",
    "sentence": "Broad stock price indexes declined over the intermeeting period.",
    "source": "minutes_20231101.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20231101",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "69531afb-9dc9-48b9-b27e-6d9b7186b691",
    "sentence": "In April, the nominal trade deficit widened, as imports picked up while exports declined slightly.",
    "source": "minutes_20170614.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170614",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c2a5c343-bcb4-4ad8-b72a-eacdb46ea499",
    "sentence": "Outside of China, indicators suggested that foreign economic activity plummeted further in the second quarter, notwithstanding some signs of improvement in May as restrictions started to ease.",
    "source": "minutes_20200610.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200610",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8875c3b9-65d4-4ed6-80f7-8cef67350314",
    "sentence": "In addition, the Bank of England established a temporary liquidity swap facility with the ECB designed to provide Ireland's central bank with sterling to help meet the potential needs of the Irish banking system.",
    "source": "minutes_20110126.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110126",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3276dd38-fc48-43e1-b53a-5863b469504e",
    "sentence": "The revision reflected data indicating a slower pace of private-sector job gains, more-subdued retail sales, a lower trajectory for personal income, greater restraint in government purchases, and weaker net exports than the staff anticipated at the time of the previous projection.",
    "source": "minutes_20120620.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120620",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fa701a13-6278-42d0-8f74-a68abb41af87",
    "sentence": "Starts of new single-family homes increased in December to their highest level since 2008, and permits for new construction also moved higher.",
    "source": "minutes_20150128.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150128",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b045d673-46d6-48c0-8b1c-7a24a52bcf63",
    "sentence": "Jeff Fuhrer and Robert H. Rasche, Executive Vice Presidents, Federal Reserve Banks of Boston and St. Louis, respectively",
    "source": "minutes_20110315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "32843c20-9f00-4725-a670-1f673dbee172",
    "sentence": "The probability that investors attach to such low interest rate scenarios could pull the expected path of the federal funds rate computed from market quotes below most Committee participants' assessments of appropriate policy as reported in the SEP.",
    "source": "minutes_20140917.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20140917",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b3ac051a-77d5-47c9-9501-9859540ff149",
    "sentence": "Participants observed that uncertainty about the economic outlook remained high. Most agreed that risks to inflation were weighted to the upside.",
    "source": "minutes_20211215.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20211215",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "77480edc-6b18-4923-a813-f5ff13774dfc",
    "sentence": "The deputy manager then discussed the possibility of a small technical realignment of the IOER rate relative to the top of the target range for the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "minutes_20180502.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180502",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8a99ec26-341e-4ad8-845e-23c5521a5809",
    "sentence": "In discussing the outlook for monetary policy over the period ahead, many participants expressed the view that it might be appropriate to raise the federal funds rate again fairly soon if incoming information on the labor market and inflation was in line with or stronger than their current expectations or if the risks of overshooting the Committee's maximum-employment and inflation objectives increased.",
    "source": "minutes_20170201.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170201",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7014219f-e3c1-4bbe-bbe5-ec7a75d51074",
    "sentence": "Continued concerns about the outlook for global economic growth weighed on commodity and foreign equity prices early in the intermeeting period.",
    "source": "minutes_20151028.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20151028",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2005d69b-1450-49d8-8d37-d1fe73936fc0",
    "sentence": "Although mortgage rates were still low and housing appeared to be relatively affordable, various factors were seen as restraining demand, including low expected income and high levels of student debt as well as difficulty in obtaining mortgage credit, particularly for younger, first-time homebuyers.",
    "source": "minutes_20140730.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20140730",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4ba357fc-b212-4fbf-99a8-f73a74180923",
    "sentence": "Contacts in some parts of the country reported continued weakness in single-family construction, while in other regions activity reportedly was picking up gradually following a sluggish summer.",
    "source": "minutes_20141029.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20141029",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "cafea5db-b5b9-426e-a31b-1ae8c4d07f55",
    "sentence": "Perhaps reflecting more subdued growth abroad, especially in Europe and China, net exports weakened in the first quarter.",
    "source": "minutes_20130501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130501",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "baac4439-76d7-49dd-99ef-787c2a95b90a",
    "sentence": "The Committee intends to review these principles and to make adjustments as appropriate at its annual organizational meeting each January, and to undertake roughly every five years a thorough public review of its monetary policy strategy, tools, and communication practices.",
    "source": "minutes_20220126.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220126",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dab72416-d51d-45ca-bc2e-6a9d54b61cae",
    "sentence": "Participants' Discussion of Policy PlanningParticipants discussedconsiderations related to the choice of the appropriate timing of the initial firming in monetary policy and pace of subsequent rate increases.",
    "source": "minutes_20150128.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150128",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "60f56921-c944-4a41-9165-415939adbfc3",
    "sentence": "The staff's forecast for inflation was little changed from the projection prepared for the January FOMC meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20130320.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b1fa244a-f811-40d3-8f4a-842f777d4321",
    "sentence": "Several participants observed that, because of the difficulties in isolating the effects of monetary policy, changes in economic structure, or increasing transparency over time regarding monetary policy decisions, the historical record did not provide definitive evidence on the length of these lags.",
    "source": "minutes_20221102.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "34673fe6-8608-41fa-b096-12a1f7183405",
    "sentence": "Participants offered their views about how much additional policy firming would likely be required for the Committee to sustainably achieve its objectives of maximum employment and 2 percent inflation. A few participants expected that policy would need to become modestly restrictive for a time and a number judged that it would be necessary to temporarily raise the federal funds rate above their assessments of its longer-run level in order to reduce the risk of a sustained overshooting of the Committee's 2 percent inflation objective or the risk posed by significant financial imbalances.",
    "source": "minutes_20180926.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180926",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b3968836-a4cc-4dcc-af30-dd88febd341c",
    "sentence": "A few participants mentioned the limited reaction in financial markets to the announcement and initial implementation of the Committee's plan for gradually reducing the Federal Reserve's securities holdings.",
    "source": "minutes_20171101.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20171101",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7596da38-5e17-4c33-bb49-53c3bab75b4b",
    "sentence": "Issuance of agency CMBS remained robust and issuance of non-agency CMBS strengthened notably in June.",
    "source": "minutes_20210728.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210728",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b7558312-d49e-47ce-a743-b57d45805da8",
    "sentence": "Consumer spending was reported to be strong in a number of areas of the country and, more broadly, appeared to be supported by rising equity and house prices, improved household balance sheets, and easier credit conditions.",
    "source": "minutes_20130501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130501",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7afb32ce-475e-4868-9ed0-580541a4c0e8",
    "sentence": "In December, the consumer price index (CPI) rose somewhat faster than in recent months, primarily reflecting an upturn in consumer energy prices; core CPI inflation remained low.",
    "source": "minutes_20140129.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20140129",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4b0d08ce-a3b2-4db6-bf3b-749adb719e23",
    "sentence": "When discussing uncertainty, various participants expressed concern about the potential effect of a prolonged government shutdown, both on near-term economic activity and on the ability to accurately assess economic conditions because of limitations to the availability of federal government data.",
    "source": "minutes_20251029.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20251029",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d76753e5-726e-4b33-8626-a8a50ed3533a",
    "sentence": "Several participants emphasized the need to ensure that banks continue to maintain strong capital levels, as lower levels of capital are typically associated with tighter credit availability from banks.",
    "source": "minutes_20201105.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20201105",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "00bc3044-bdbb-424d-b60d-cf98e251500b",
    "sentence": "To purchase and sell foreign currencies (also known as cable transfers) at home and abroad in the open market, including with the United States Treasury, with foreign monetary authorities, with the Bank for International Settlements, and with other entities in the open market.",
    "source": "minutes_20220126.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220126",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f5b49184-b23f-4dc4-918a-073ebdfa58b3",
    "sentence": "Developments in Financial Markets and the Federal Reserve's Balance SheetIn a joint session of the Committee and the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, the manager of the System Open Market Account (SOMA) reported on developments in domestic and foreign financial markets.",
    "source": "minutes_20150128.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150128",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d6315cb2-eb70-49bc-90ce-80c6cbef9ba7",
    "sentence": "Automakers' schedules indicated that the pace of motor vehicle assemblies in the coming months would be a bit below that in March.",
    "source": "minutes_20130501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130501",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dd57e10f-ed38-4e53-a374-95f9f1fedcf3",
    "sentence": "Most major global equity price indexes declined, on net, and EME sovereign spreads widened modestly.",
    "source": "minutes_20190619.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190619",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3c308b16-50d4-4412-b0f8-a606d9f0ca54",
    "sentence": "A few participants expressed concerns that in the current environment of increased uncertainty, the policy rate projections prepared as part of the Summary of Economic Projections (SEP) do not accurately convey the Committee's policy outlook.",
    "source": "minutes_20190130.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190130",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0db6a605-313b-4bca-bced-8843b6bc7e43",
    "sentence": "Particularly in light of persistent low readings on inflation and from indicators of inflation expectations along with the risks to the U.S. outlook associated with global economic developments, he noted that a policy rate reduction at the current meeting would help re-center inflation and inflation expectations at levels consistent with the Committee's symmetric 2 percent inflation objective and simultaneously provide some insurance against unexpected developments that could slow U.S. economic growth.",
    "source": "minutes_20190619.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190619",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d8757015-50cf-44bc-939e-24ccb6387826",
    "sentence": "Broad domestic equity prices were little changed, on net, amid high market volatility, while corporate bond yields increased notably.",
    "source": "minutes_20221102.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a208105f-c972-4f19-8d7f-7e8f430f55ad",
    "sentence": "Accordingly, Ms. George preferred to signal a near-term tapering of asset purchases, which would begin to move policy toward a more appropriate stance.",
    "source": "minutes_20130501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130501",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d2648fed-5f33-4048-8477-cb797a014eea",
    "sentence": "Participants' Views on Current Conditions and the Economic OutlookIn their discussion of the economic situation and the outlook, meeting participants saw the information received over the intermeeting period as suggesting that economic activity had been expanding moderately.",
    "source": "minutes_20151028.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20151028",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "91a05446-c2c4-4157-94c6-e1632247e8ef",
    "sentence": "Some contacts reported they were increasing capital budgets to undertake investment that had been postponed during the recession and early stages of the recovery; in some cases, firms were planning to expand capacity.",
    "source": "minutes_20110315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "40f8e3fd-4298-457f-8c6b-261a5bf470f0",
    "sentence": "Still, with an accommodative stance of policy, most participants continued to anticipate that inflation would stabilize around the Committee's 2 percent objective over the medium term.",
    "source": "minutes_20171101.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20171101",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "26394740-d119-4d60-8073-beb4f866a6e6",
    "sentence": "In addition, various participants noted that clear communications with the public are central to the efficacy of all policy tools and that, therefore, the Committee should complete its monetary policy framework review in the near term, including revising the Statement on Longer-Run Goals and Monetary Policy Strategy.",
    "source": "minutes_20200610.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200610",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4ee41ac6-2aee-431e-aa74-4a76ba152604",
    "sentence": "However, it was noted that the intermeeting period had also witnessed some more-positive news on labor market conditions, including a further increase in the rate of job openings.",
    "source": "minutes_20150429.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150429",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "98253c27-1172-4a6a-938f-12ae147dae88",
    "sentence": "Foreign economic growth slowed in the second quarter, as troubles in the property sector weighed on economic activity in China and monetary policy restraint contributed to the slowing in economic growth in Europe.",
    "source": "minutes_20230920.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230920",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e9f0313d-869d-4186-8455-c1bdb3b3d398",
    "sentence": "Domestic equity prices edged up, and corporate bond spreads narrowed a little.",
    "source": "minutes_20210616.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210616",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9c834cf2-5174-4ec3-baa6-a4dfe383d6a2",
    "sentence": "In this participant's view, a 50 basis point cut would preserve space for further cuts in the target range that could be implemented when market conditions had improved enough to ensure that the monetary policy transmission mechanism was functioning.",
    "source": "minutes_20200315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "92ba9147-6e90-4d57-a550-48a59f066409",
    "sentence": "A few participants expressed concern that longer-run inflation expectations would remain low, particularly if economic growth slowed more than expected.",
    "source": "minutes_20181219.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20181219",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "eadca9ba-5337-4da7-a6d9-81b8bd3a3c55",
    "sentence": "However, with longer-term interest rates already very low, there did not appear to be a need for enhanced forward guidance at this juncture or much scope for forward guidance to put additional downward pressure on yields.",
    "source": "minutes_20200916.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200916",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9d1769e2-d234-456e-a985-84385974f6b0",
    "sentence": "Real federal government purchases appeared to decrease further in January and February, as defense spending continued to contract on balance.",
    "source": "minutes_20130320.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f493a305-649d-44b6-8e0d-8f2e207ad238",
    "sentence": "In their discussion of the household sector, participants observed that real consumer spending had declined in November and December -- in part reflecting the tightening in financial conditions over the past year -- and anticipated that consumption would likely grow at a subdued rate in 2023.",
    "source": "minutes_20230201.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230201",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f67ba44c-adcb-4f89-ac7c-68c87dcb474c",
    "sentence": "Business debt levels were high before the pandemic, and the ability of some businesses to service these obligations will depend on the course of the economic recovery.",
    "source": "minutes_20201105.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20201105",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4dea3765-10ce-40a9-9ac5-7e0398b0380c",
    "sentence": "The staff noted that the Committee had previously indicated that, in the longer run, it intends to operate with no more securities holdings than necessary to implement monetary policy efficiently and effectively.",
    "source": "minutes_20190130.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190130",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2ab755ae-a5c0-47e6-a521-17ed7119608b",
    "sentence": "Inflation had moderated, and longer-term inflation expectations remained stable.",
    "source": "minutes_20111213.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20111213",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7d67f0cd-38ce-4d71-b8a5-8b4a20f0e7e0",
    "sentence": "Looking further ahead, participants expected inflation to be at levels consistent with achieving the Committee's objectives over time.",
    "source": "minutes_20210428.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210428",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "be7f2fce-39c2-4b19-aaf2-7d153e9d92ed",
    "sentence": "In their comments on labor market conditions, participants cited strong employment gains, low levels of unemployment in their Districts, reports of shortages of workers in various industries, or firming in wage increases.",
    "source": "minutes_20160127.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160127",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a2dcbd58-53ef-4026-b63a-9c072a418337",
    "sentence": "Many indicated that they expected cyclical pressures associated with a tightening labor market to show through to higher inflation over the medium term.",
    "source": "minutes_20171213.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20171213",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d39c1e57-287d-4954-95b0-13a455734144",
    "sentence": "Developments in Financial Markets and the Federal Reserve's Balance SheetThe Manager of the System Open Market Account (SOMA) reported on developments in domestic and foreign financial markets during the period since the Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) met on July 31-August 1, 2012.",
    "source": "minutes_20120913.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120913",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8d9acc05-6f78-4a7d-bdbb-570a87532719",
    "sentence": "Although international travel recovered further in May, exports and imports of services remained depressed relative to pre-pandemic levels.",
    "source": "minutes_20210728.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210728",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "703d01f6-eaf3-466b-a308-ce4b9d1923bd",
