    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "30460bc9-f76c-42d2-aa86-34ffeb9be9fa",
    "sentence": "Many participants noted that the slowing in these components of core inflation corroborated reports received from their business contacts that firms were more reluctant to increase prices, as consumers appeared to be more price sensitive and were increasingly seeking discounts.",
    "source": "minutes_20241107.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20241107",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "42033fb1-262a-4742-a4e4-3f4c757a1ed5",
    "sentence": "In these circumstances, she believed it appropriate to gradually increase the target range for the federal funds rate from its current low level, which would allow monetary policy to continue to lend support to the economic expansion.",
    "source": "minutes_20161102.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20161102",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ad29f288-3b0a-48ea-9ff0-66f115c38ad0",
    "sentence": "Real personal consumption expenditures (PCE) rose moderately in August.",
    "source": "minutes_20131030.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20131030",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "62a63a47-6bde-44af-80fe-258f8680ea0e",
    "sentence": "Market participants characterized the Federal Reserve's monetary policy communications over the intermeeting period as suggesting a slightly more accommodative policy stance than had been expected.",
    "source": "minutes_20140730.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20140730",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9d969986-9f80-4bfb-9fc2-05dbf62539b9",
    "sentence": "The manager noted that current financial conditions appeared to be providing neither a headwind nor tailwind to growth.",
    "source": "minutes_20240731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240731",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5094d12d-22e7-47f5-8b10-c5d5b12b0ad5",
    "sentence": "Nominal yields on Treasury securities declined over the period.",
    "source": "minutes_20160615.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160615",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "22e2aaea-c897-498c-a45e-4c7d9e980291",
    "sentence": "Total nonfarm payroll employment increased at a robust pace during those two months.",
    "source": "minutes_20230614.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230614",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "75a37eda-e4f0-4acb-9230-5f715a34703d",
    "sentence": "In the absence of material take-up at the ON RRP facility, and assuming balance sheet runoff would end, the staff estimated that reserves would continue to gradually decline amid projected increases in other Federal Reserve liabilities.",
    "source": "minutes_20251029.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20251029",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "40bd2059-51c9-4b09-924f-dd3239c8201c",
    "sentence": "While business contacts in a number of Districts continued to report that the pace of wage increases had picked up, recent national readings on hourly compensation and average hourly earnings of employees had remained subdued.",
    "source": "minutes_20150729.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150729",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "79c67335-027b-4dc7-81d2-fc4ff2174d66",
    "sentence": "The staff viewed the risks of upside inflationary pressures as having increased since the previous forecast and now saw the risks to the inflation projection as balanced.",
    "source": "minutes_20210317.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210317",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5a9aaeeb-3be4-4dd2-814b-fb0d32482b69",
    "sentence": "On a four-quarter change basis, total PCE price inflation was expected to be 5.5 percent in 2022, while core inflation was expected to be 4.7 percent, both lower than in the November projection.",
    "source": "minutes_20221214.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20221214",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bedb6603-2397-48f5-91dc-9bba3c6a0bfc",
    "sentence": "The rise in nominal U.S. Treasury yields was associated with an increase in inflation compensation that, in turn, seemed to reflect a firming in inflation data as well as a notable rise in crude oil prices.",
    "source": "minutes_20180502.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180502",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "acefd1ff-7de4-448c-87da-0189021a59d5",
    "sentence": "The rate of private-sector job openings continued to be elevated in June and July, while the rate of quits moved higher on balance; initial claims for unemployment insurance benefits were at a historically low level in mid-September.",
    "source": "minutes_20180926.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180926",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fdafbe99-9ca6-49cf-8921-347d43ed2151",
    "sentence": "Many participants noted the substantial rise in one- and three-year measures of inflation expectations in the Federal Reserve Bank of New York's Survey of Consumer Expectations or in the one-year measure in the University of Michigan Surveys of Consumers.",
    "source": "minutes_20210922.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210922",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "836ba118-59ec-488c-aa99-ba0fd579fcf1",
    "sentence": "Overall conditions in the labor market were gradually improving, and the unemployment rate continued to decline, although it remained elevated relative to levels that the Committee judged to be consistent, over the longer run, with its statutory mandate of maximum employment and price stability.",
    "source": "minutes_20110427.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110427",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c968a1f8-f9b4-4f83-a49b-53d930ccafb1",
    "sentence": "Trading conditions for Treasury securities and MBS were impaired. Moreover, primary issuance of investment-grade corporate bonds was sporadic, and that of speculative-grade corporate bonds and leveraged loans virtually stopped after late February.",
    "source": "minutes_20200315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200315",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "435965d0-e0b6-4480-ab34-3a45d233f32e",
    "sentence": "Participants judged that the pace and extent of policy rate increases would continue to depend on the implications of incoming information for the outlook for economic activity and inflation and on risks to the outlook.",
    "source": "minutes_20220921.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220921",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d567655f-c00a-4703-9b89-79cf885e35a6",
    "sentence": "Participants remarked that a moderation in labor market conditions would likely involve a decline in the number of job openings as well as a moderate increase in unemployment from the current very low rate.",
    "source": "minutes_20220727.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220727",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "29cffc9b-7ad0-4024-b714-8234f87da093",
    "sentence": "Several participants favored including such additional information in the policy statement to be released following the current meeting; several others indicated that providing such information would be most useful when the time came for the Committee to begin reducing the pace of its securities purchases, reasoning that earlier inclusion might trigger an unintended tightening of financial conditions.",
    "source": "minutes_20130731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130731",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f9792926-eb33-4c27-9391-298b5d33ce2a",
    "sentence": "The staff presentations considered two key channels by which monetary policy influences inflation--the response of inflation to changes in resource utilization and the role of inflation expectations, or trend inflation, in the price-setting process.",
    "source": "minutes_20180131.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180131",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9b67448d-48a6-4b43-baf2-add2340e2c69",
    "sentence": "Finally, the staff presentation noted that the Committee would need to decide if and when to use the tools that it has developed to temporarily reduce reserve balances--reverse repurchase agreements and term deposits--in order to tighten the correspondence between any changes in the interest rate the Federal Reserve pays on excess reserves and the changes in the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "minutes_20110427.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110427",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ac29f30f-3cde-4a4f-9ce1-2fab8ef76d4c",
    "sentence": "Participants stressed the major downside risk that the spread of the virus might intensify in those areas of the country currently less affected, thereby sidelining many more U.S. workers and further damping purchases by consumers.",
    "source": "minutes_20200315.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200315",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e745c821-9416-4cdb-a733-8000505ef106",
    "sentence": "In their discussion of monetary policy for the period ahead, members agreed that no changes to the Committee's asset purchase program or to its target range for the federal funds rate were warranted at this meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20110126.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110126",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6212dcc0-d18f-4cb9-a2c3-0ef916d06ec8",
    "sentence": "The Committee also decided to maintain its existing policy of reinvesting principal payments from its holdings of agency debt and agency mortgage-backed securities in agency mortgage-backed securities and of rolling over maturing Treasury securities at auction, and it anticipated doing so until normalization of the level of the federal funds rate is well under way. Members noted that this policy, by keeping the Committee's holdings of longer-term securities at sizable levels, should help maintain accommodative financial conditions.",
    "source": "minutes_20170201.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170201",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a4c87043-656d-4a3c-9e71-885f75f58217",
    "sentence": "Shipments and orders of nondefense capital goods had been on a steady uptrend over the first eight months of 2017.",
    "source": "minutes_20170920.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170920",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "06e58728-0593-406b-87fd-18bffaf0e809",
    "sentence": "In the credit card market, lending standards at commercial banks tightened further according to the July SLOOS.",
    "source": "minutes_20200729.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200729",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "db085dea-1fa8-46c6-b9ff-a056144fe8de",
    "sentence": "Bank lending for residential mortgages was solid in the fourth quarter, and the issuance of mortgage-backed securities was robust.",
    "source": "minutes_20170201.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170201",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5f892951-5fff-4b87-a2e2-cd9a107bb5ef",
    "sentence": "Spreads of yields on Italian and Spanish government debt over those on German bunds narrowed over the intermeeting period, with spreads on shorter-term debt falling particularly noticeably.",
    "source": "minutes_20120125.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20120125",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bc3bc48d-c4f5-4070-88d4-7fc7c2639e3a",
    "sentence": "Various participants noted the importance of the Committee clearly communicating its assessment of progress toward its longer-run goals well in advance of the time when it could be judged substantial enough to warrant a change in the pace of purchases.",
    "source": "minutes_20210127.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210127",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "73b6bec6-76cb-430e-9808-a50b5998ba02",
    "sentence": "For some participants, the greater upside risks to economic growth, the upward movement in inflation compensation over recent months, or the possibility of further increases in oil prices had increased the upside risks to their inflation forecasts. However, several others pointed out that a further rise in the dollar might continue to hold down inflation.",
    "source": "minutes_20161214.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20161214",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "79d31887-1376-4d8b-b03e-e289642470f5",
    "sentence": "Use of the overnight reverse repo (ON RRP) facility declined slightly over the intermeeting period.",
    "source": "minutes_20240731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240731",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "69a5efc8-5917-496d-8639-453362d241cb",
    "sentence": "Services inflation, however, remained high in some of those economies.",
    "source": "minutes_20241218.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20241218",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "28de397a-d0c0-4364-874d-29bdbd4f6a6d",
    "sentence": "The manager turned next to a discussion of money markets and Federal Reserve operations.",
    "source": "minutes_20210922.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210922",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c2f5e8b5-9187-4bfd-9a48-b31f5f0c38f2",
    "sentence": "Total industrial production plunged in April, as many factories slowed or suspended operation in response to the coronavirus pandemic.",
    "source": "minutes_20200610.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200610",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3430d60d-9dce-4157-a9be-996191a3258f",
    "sentence": "The March data, together with revised estimates for earlier months, indicated that real exports grew briskly in the first quarter and at a faster pace than in the second half of 2016.",
    "source": "minutes_20170614.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170614",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e9c65ba5-1dc6-49ae-97db-9e06e2c2c299",
    "sentence": "Interest rates for credit card offers inched up in February, while those on new auto loans were little changed over the intermeeting period on net.",
    "source": "minutes_20250507.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20250507",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "240ed0f5-7db3-4049-858b-3930c8f5f9fb",
    "sentence": "Most participants remarked that they saw benefits in reducing the pace of net purchases of Treasury securities and agency MBS proportionally in order to end both sets of purchases at the same time. These participants observed that such an approach would be consistent with the Committee's understanding that purchases of Treasury securities and agency MBS had similar effects on broader financial conditions and played similar roles in the transmission of monetary policy, or that these purchases were not intended as credit allocation.",
    "source": "minutes_20210728.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210728",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4875a79b-6b12-41a7-9da3-9cb0a75fa751",
    "sentence": "Market-based measures of inflation compensation remained low.",
    "source": "minutes_20191030.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20191030",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "48e2f30c-1fd5-4bf1-b847-87c5f8274d0a",
    "sentence": "Market expectations for the path of the federal funds rate were little changed over the intermeeting period.",
    "source": "minutes_20170201.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170201",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8f1bbbb2-2a70-401f-863c-7ff893add8b8",
    "sentence": "The manager indicated that some repos might be needed at least through April, when tax payments will sharply reduce reserve levels.",
    "source": "minutes_20191211.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20191211",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "933f0750-e5a5-41ff-a1c5-efe10292cc78",
    "sentence": "One member preferred a reduction in the target range of 50 basis points in the federal funds rate at this meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20190918.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190918",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3c7b5b78-d1e8-41a9-ad05-03b0dffbc452",
    "sentence": "They also agreed that household spending had been increasing at a moderate rate, and that the housing sector had improved further; however, business fixed investment and net exports had been soft.",
    "source": "minutes_20160316.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160316",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ebb0cffb-4769-4129-afa9-917574d06b08",
    "sentence": "Yield spreads on EME sovereign bonds edged down.",
    "source": "minutes_20170920.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170920",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8b3ffb6c-a718-4710-aa9f-b4a8c60a9bdf",
    "sentence": "Demand improved as social-distancing restrictions were lifted in the United Kingdom and the euro area following the rollout of vaccines.",
    "source": "minutes_20210616.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210616",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6fe47d24-89e6-4fb6-a489-c665a14ff108",
    "sentence": "Supply chain disruptions associated with the earthquake in Japan continued to hinder production at motor vehicle manufacturers and the firms that supply them.",
    "source": "minutes_20110809.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20110809",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0213f44e-7148-47c3-be04-f088882fbd8c",
    "sentence": "The unemployment rate for African Americans declined and the Hispanic unemployment rate rose; both rates remained well above the national average. However, the Asian unemployment rate moved below the national average in December.",
    "source": "minutes_20210127.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210127",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bc8c9960-f935-4fc5-9f73-33aa949433ba",
    "sentence": "Some participants highlighted the fact that price increases had become more widespread.",
    "source": "minutes_20211103.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20211103",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "79545e80-300f-4846-96ab-b3be9370719c",
    "sentence": "Indicators of near-term labor market conditions were consistent with projections of moderate increases in employment in the coming months: Measures of job openings generally moved up, but the rate of gross private-sector hiring and indicators of firms' hiring plans were subdued, on balance, and initial claims for unemployment insurance trended up a little over the intermeeting period.",
    "source": "minutes_20130501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130501",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "25f81c0b-c279-4ff6-9c24-40d9b95755e3",
    "sentence": "Inflation had increased in recent quarters but was still below the Committee's 2 percent longer-run objective.",
    "source": "minutes_20170201.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170201",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "cb670cb1-b80a-4975-a340-d76de2b4fbab",
    "sentence": "One-month-ahead option-implied volatility on the S&P 500 index--the VIX--was little changed, on net, at levels close to historical lows.",
    "source": "minutes_20171213.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20171213",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f0bbba84-8e62-4811-a131-e0b6a03463a4",
    "sentence": "A few of these participants also suggested that a near-term change to reinvestment policy could be misinterpreted as signifying that the Committee had shifted toward a less gradual approach to overall policy normalization.",
    "source": "minutes_20170614.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170614",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2b68aabc-9a78-47ce-9307-c3b1deea62d1",
    "sentence": "On net, inflation compensation moved up at both the 5-year and the 5-to-10-year horizons, and both measures returned to levels seen in early 2017 before the string of generally weaker-than-expected inflation readings.",
    "source": "minutes_20180131.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180131",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aac58f47-da15-42ef-9845-a43227a8edd8",
    "sentence": "In light of the considerable progress to date toward the Committee's maximum-employment objective and the implications of that progress for the outlook for inflation, members agreed to remove from the forward guidance in the postmeeting statement the indication that the Committee judges that it can be patient in beginning to normalize the stance of monetary policy and to indicate instead that the Committee anticipates that it will be appropriate to raise the target range for the federal funds rate when it has seen further improvement in the labor market and is reasonably confident that inflation will move back to its 2 percent objective over the medium term.",
    "source": "minutes_20150318.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150318",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "664eb323-f6e8-47ac-a359-937dc4521e6a",
    "sentence": "Nevertheless, participants judged that uncertainty about their forecast of real GDP growth remained high. Moreover, a number of participants noted that structural factors such as technological progress and higher productivity growth, possibly reflecting increasing use of AI, could boost economic growth without generating price pressures and could also damp job creation.",
    "source": "minutes_20251210.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20251210",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f2231246-4e76-4558-96de-7df7dce69d0c",
    "sentence": "Incoming information pointed to stable, low inflation that was running a little below the Committee's longer-run goal of 2 percent.",
    "source": "minutes_20121212.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20121212",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "85eff21e-c7b2-4203-80e1-7f97fb86015e",
    "sentence": "Subsequent communications from FOMC participants were interpreted as suggesting that the FOMC would be patient in assessing the implications of recent economic and financial developments.",
    "source": "minutes_20190130.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190130",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7b5d5ced-d38f-426c-ab95-5ac529fe2b16",
    "sentence": "No decisions regarding the Committee's approach were made at the meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20211215.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20211215",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a1b1d6f7-2ff0-4167-b091-73c981594c0d",
    "sentence": "On the one hand, the participation rate for prime-age males remained significantly below its level before the financial crisis, suggesting that it could rise further over time. In addition, there was some uncertainty around estimates of the longer-run trend rate of labor force participation and it could be higher than previously thought, reflecting, for example, a shift toward later retirement.",
    "source": "minutes_20161102.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20161102",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ba5b58d1-74c3-46e7-a8af-c6373fca226c",
    "sentence": "Aggregate foreign economic growth appeared to pick up in the third quarter amid signs of recovery of oil production in Canada and of improved manufacturing production in Mexico. However, weaker investment readings pointed to a slight moderation of economic activity in China in the third quarter.",
    "source": "minutes_20160921.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20160921",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8576dc14-48a6-4e55-9d5a-a318905743ae",
    "sentence": "Financing conditions remained moderately restrictive, as borrowing costs remained elevated despite declining over the intermeeting period.",
    "source": "minutes_20231213.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20231213",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "32143de7-3f7d-4794-adef-be9f96c21cde",
    "sentence": "But some others believed that labor market slack in addition to that measured by the unemployment rate remained and that further progress was possible before labor market conditions were fully consistent with the Committee's objective of maximum employment.",
    "source": "minutes_20150917.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150917",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "97de0fc6-c75b-4877-a59b-7ae558d41fd9",
    "sentence": "A couple of participants cited risks associated with high levels of corporate borrowing.",
    "source": "minutes_20251029.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20251029",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "819cb6ce-fe55-4fed-94f4-91aae15bfb75",
    "sentence": "After assessing the outlook for economic activity, the labor market, and inflation and weighing the uncertainties associated with the outlook, members agreed to raise the target range for the federal funds rate to 1/4 to 1/2 percent at this meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20151216.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20151216",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "60d719ea-682d-4a94-b6eb-6cf350bdabd5",
    "sentence": "The increases in nonfarm payroll employment in July and August remained well above the pace likely to be sustainable in the longer run.",
    "source": "minutes_20170920.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20170920",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d11c5007-f2ae-4da6-9e4d-a0d0d5e04220",
    "sentence": "Household credit quality stayed broadly solid but continued to worsen for some types of credit owed by borrowers with low credit scores.",
    "source": "minutes_20220921.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220921",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "53a383ca-1647-4fc5-a345-cc7de6d77367",
    "sentence": "Since then, the size of the Federal Reserve's balance sheet had declined substantially. In addition, money market conditions had tightened recently, which suggested that reserve balances may be moving closer to ample. In light of these developments, participants discussed whether to stop balance sheet runoff soon and what the maturity composition of the SOMA Treasury portfolio (SOMA portfolio) should be in the longer run.",
    "source": "minutes_20251029.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20251029",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a3e5d176-d40d-40a3-a72c-197f260822d4",
    "sentence": "Regarding downside risks to economic activity, participants noted the possibility that the cumulative and rapid tightening of monetary policy would eventually affect economic activity more than expected, and that the additional effects of the tightening of bank credit conditions could prove more substantial than anticipated.",
    "source": "minutes_20230614.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230614",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "325d99cd-2812-4586-80c9-2db65f8d8d49",
    "sentence": "The forward guidance also reiterated the Committee's expectation that, even after employment and inflation are near mandate-consistent levels, economic conditions may, for some time, warrant keeping the target federal funds rate below levels the Committee views as normal in the longer run.",
    "source": "minutes_20140917.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20140917",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9183e423-f0da-4be0-9a07-a145075731a3",
    "sentence": "In the commercial real estate (CRE) sector, financing conditions remained generally accommodative despite a modest deceleration in bank loan growth.",
    "source": "minutes_20190731.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190731",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "615cb343-26a3-4268-a620-ea3d044548ae",
    "sentence": "From his work on r*, to the balance sheet, to leading the steering committee for our monetary policy review, Thomas Laubach's intellectual fingerprints are all over the Committee's decisions that will define this era of the Federal Reserve.",
    "source": "minutes_20200916.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200916",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7fe99c7d-f8eb-49da-ac65-0648ea9e9b8d",
    "sentence": "Vulnerabilities stemming from funding risk were characterized as moderate.",
    "source": "minutes_20200129.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20200129",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "591bb384-6c55-48ab-908d-cdd9b18b80a6",
    "sentence": "These decreases reflected notable step-downs in both energy and core inflation amid slowing aggregate demand and declines in oil prices.",
    "source": "minutes_20231213.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20231213",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b4f34c1e-63af-4a5f-a5b2-b721403e91da",
    "sentence": "Consumer sentiment in the Thomson Reuters/University of Michigan Surveys of Consumers rose somewhat in February, but it declined in early March and remained relatively downbeat.",
    "source": "minutes_20130320.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130320",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "df72fd72-3997-4751-a78c-f0df8101d388",
    "sentence": "Some also expressed interest in studying, over the longer term, approaches in which the Committee would target a mixture of secured and unsecured rates.",
    "source": "minutes_20181108.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20181108",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "66e214ff-413e-4d19-a084-2029c767f363",
    "sentence": "A straight read of federal funds futures rates suggested that market participants were placing higher odds on significant policy easing in 2024 than they did just before the December FOMC meeting.",
    "source": "minutes_20240131.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240131",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e06a065d-a306-433b-b50e-3c49ea3b546e",
    "sentence": "Higher rates had reportedly made repos a more attractive alternative investment for major lenders in the federal funds market, thus reducing the availability of funding in that market and putting some upward pressure on the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "minutes_20180502.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180502",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "da49a836-5e3b-4af3-9073-3f1b2faba34a",
    "sentence": "These restrictions weakened retail sales and contributed to labor shortages and transportation congestion, disrupting global supply chains.",
    "source": "minutes_20210922.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210922",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "22d309eb-2c02-4972-89c6-094988ca491d",
    "sentence": "Members also agreed to several adjustments in the description of the outlook for the economy and monetary policy.",
    "source": "minutes_20190130.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20190130",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7beb2bda-d740-4e8d-aa4c-91d38878c47a",
    "sentence": "Consistent with the general improvement in financial market sentiment, most foreign currencies appreciated against the dollar as flight-to-safety flows reversed.",
    "source": "minutes_20140319.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20140319",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aa0ef0ef-2904-46f4-8575-4a22fccf2170",
    "sentence": "Demand for housing appeared to have remained very strong, but incoming data suggested that materials shortages and a lack of developed lots for construction were restraining residential building activity.",
    "source": "minutes_20210922.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210922",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bc78bc62-8683-4cfe-924d-a74d077a2b27",
    "sentence": "As of May, total payroll employment had retraced two‑thirds of the job losses seen at the onset of the pandemic, although employment in the leisure and hospitality sector and in the education sector (including both public and private education) had bounced back by less.",
    "source": "minutes_20210616.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20210616",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dda07a6b-672e-40c0-acca-eeed906d1aa1",
    "sentence": "Various participants mentioned a willingness to tighten policy further should risks to inflation materialize in a way that such an action became appropriate.",
    "source": "minutes_20240501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240501",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6e6d00a0-148e-428c-98a7-8c3eb43fe04d",
    "sentence": "Participants generally continued to see recent fiscal policy changes as supportive of economic growth over the next few years, and a few indicated that fiscal policy posed an upside risk.",
    "source": "minutes_20180613.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20180613",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3fc8fde4-7a8d-47ca-ba46-d5f2f7d18a36",
    "sentence": "But with inflation still well above the Committee's longer-run goal and the labor market remaining tight, most participants continued to see upside risks to inflation. These risks included the imbalance of aggregate demand and supply persisting longer than expected, as well as risks emanating from global oil markets, the potential for upside shocks to food prices, the effects of a strong housing market on shelter inflation, and the potential for more limited declines in goods prices.",
    "source": "minutes_20230920.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230920",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0c0774f0-57a7-4ff9-a7ff-7acc2683cf25",
    "sentence": "Purchasing and selling obligations of, or fully guaranteed as to principal and interest by, a foreign government or agency thereof (\"Permitted Foreign Securities\") through outright purchases and sales;",
    "source": "minutes_20220126.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20220126",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "871c7212-4465-4f29-a99e-1a320e573879",
    "sentence": "Some participants saw the possibility that an extended period during which labor markets remained relatively tight could continue to shrink remaining margins of underutilization, including the still-high level of prime-age workers outside the labor force and elevated levels of involuntary part-time employment and long-duration unemployment.",
    "source": "minutes_20161214.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20161214",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bff5b557-c197-4677-a0db-555746a6dfb4",
    "sentence": "Credit remained available for most consumers, despite some signs of recent tightening.",
    "source": "minutes_20240501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240501",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "935f6ced-f770-4d9b-8156-5409fd94f5ab",
    "sentence": "Real state and local government purchases appeared to be rising in the second quarter, with increases in both payrolls and nominal construction spending in recent months.",
    "source": "minutes_20150617.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150617",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "def71ebb-a245-468e-89ef-d418b7676b08",
    "sentence": "The average delinquency rate for loans in CMBS pools ticked down in March but remained at elevated levels.",
    "source": "minutes_20240501.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240501",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8bec776a-7e78-41b6-b5f6-4074534bdaae",
    "sentence": "Export declines were concentrated in capital goods, particularly aircraft.",
    "source": "minutes_20150128.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150128",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "cf576505-37bd-43f4-9816-4dee25493969",
    "sentence": "Over the intermeeting period, some softer-than-expected data releases appeared to lessen the perception among investors that policy may need to tighten further in order to bring inflation down to 2 percent over time.",
    "source": "minutes_20231213.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20231213",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0d5c4725-e091-4ca1-9f22-86143106a093",
    "sentence": "The longer-run projections represent each participant's assessment of the rate to which each variable would be expected to converge, over time, under appropriate monetary policy and in the absence of further shocks to the economy.",
    "source": "minutes_20150318.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150318",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8672a296-9590-489e-b24b-9de75b215041",
    "sentence": "Participants remarked that demand and supply in the labor market had continued to come into better balance.",
    "source": "minutes_20240612.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20240612",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ef480ce5-7b29-4e09-9fc4-56822afbf946",
    "sentence": "A few participants raised the possibility that recent declines in inflation might suggest that the economic recovery was not as strong as some thought.",
    "source": "minutes_20131218.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20131218",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "cad58fb0-1b90-4e16-84d9-a95617c3b120",
    "sentence": "But a few participants noted that the risk remained that inflationary pressures could rise as the expansion continued, especially if monetary policy remained highly accommodative for too long.",
    "source": "minutes_20130320.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20130320",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "31bfa589-cd91-4b42-b732-59a76aa2f0d0",
    "sentence": "Most participants also believed that, as part of the process of clarifying the Committee's future policy intentions, it would be appropriate at this time for the Committee to provide additional guidance in its postmeeting statement regarding the likely behavior of the federal funds rate after its first increase. For example, the statement could indicate that the Committee currently anticipates that, even after employment and inflation are near mandate-consistent levels, economic conditions may, for some time, warrant keeping the target federal funds rate below levels the Committee views as normal in the longer run.",
    "source": "minutes_20140319.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20140319",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e7bfe06e-b3ae-4dca-84c7-1e4cf898612f",
    "sentence": "Inflation abroad continued to ease.",
    "source": "minutes_20250129.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20250129",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f474d0a3-b4bf-4538-bbd7-5931f428008b",
    "sentence": "Measures of inflation expectations from the Open Market Desk's Survey of Primary Dealers and Survey of Market Participants moved higher at shorter horizons and were little changed at longer horizons.",
    "source": "minutes_20230322.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20230322",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "48e53b6f-8f8d-43e4-b0da-2fa0d68d8858",
    "sentence": "Some participants also discussed the risk that a possible divergence in interest rates in the United States and abroad might lead to further appreciation of the dollar, extending the downward pressure on commodity prices and the weakness in net exports.",
    "source": "minutes_20150729.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20150729",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "632a5254-5826-4bb6-a561-088ddf932d30",
    "sentence": "Short-term funding markets were adversely affected for a time by concerns about potential delays in raising the federal debt limit.",
    "source": "minutes_20131030.html",
    "doc_type": "minutes",
    "date": "20131030",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7990dfc8-4f88-4821-a351-5f4a21cd3b57",
    "sentence": "Participants noted that tariff effects were becoming more apparent in the data, as indicated by recent increases in goods price inflation, while services price inflation had continued to slow.",
    "source": "minutes_20250730.html",
